#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:3
msgid "CI Enforcement"
msgstr "Wymuszanie w CI"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:8
msgid "Pre-commit hook"
msgstr "Hook pre-commit"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:10
msgid "The simplest CI integration. Add to ``.pre-commit-config.yaml``:"
msgstr "Najprostsza integracja z CI. Dodaj do ``.pre-commit-config.yaml``:"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:20
msgid ""
"This runs ``snapper --in-place`` on changed files matching ``.org``, "
"``.tex``, ``.md``, and ``.txt``."
msgstr ""
"Uruchamia ``snapper --in-place`` na zmienionych plikach pasujących do "
"``.org``, ``.tex``, ``.md`` i ``.txt``."

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:23
msgid "GitHub Actions"
msgstr "GitHub Actions"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:25
msgid "Add a formatting check step to your CI workflow:"
msgstr "Dodaj krok sprawdzania formatowania do swojego workflow CI:"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:34
msgid ""
"The ``--check`` flag exits with code 1 if any file needs reformatting, "
"without modifying anything."
msgstr ""
"Flaga ``--check`` kończy działanie z kodem 1, jeśli jakikolwiek plik "
"wymaga przeformatowania, bez modyfikowania czegokolwiek."

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:37
msgid "Preview changes in CI"
msgstr "Podgląd zmian w CI"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:39
msgid "Use ``--diff`` to show what would change:"
msgstr "Użyj ``--diff``, aby wyświetlić planowane zmiany:"

#: ../../source/howto/ci-enforcement.rst:46
msgid "This prints a unified diff to stdout, useful for PR review comments."
msgstr "Wypisuje ujednolicony diff na stdout, przydatny do komentarzy w przeglądzie PR."

